Description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION OF THE BIOENERGY ASSOCIATION OF CALIFORNIA AND THE RURAL COUNTY REPRESENTATIVES OF CALIFORNIA Pursuant to Rules 8.2 and 8.4 of Commissions Rules of Practice and Procedure, the Bioenergy Association of California (BAC) and the Rural County Representatives of California (RCRC) hereby give notice of an ex parte communication that occurred via WebEx on Wednesday, January 29, 2025, at 1pm.  The ex parte communication was a meeting between Commissioner John Reynolds energy advisor, Carolyn Chen, BACs Executive Director, Julia Levin, and RCRC Policy Advocates John Kennedy and Leigh Kammerich.  The other meeting participants (who are not parties to this Rulemaking) included Thomas Jordan (CEO, Scotts Valley Energy Corp, Scotts Valley Band of Pomo Indians), Bruce Springsteen (Air Quality Engineer for Placer County Air Pollution Control District), and Greg Kester (Director of Renewable Resource Programs, California Association of Sanitation Agencies).

Filed By: Rural County Representatives of California,Bioenergy Association of California

The communication will be a meeting via WebEx with Commissioner John Reynolds staff to discuss issues related to the BioMAT program.  The meeting participants are expected to be Maria Sotero (Commissioner Reynolds energy advisor), Bruce Springsteen (Air Quality Engineer for Placer County Air Pollution Control District), John Kennedy and Leigh Kammerich (Policy Advocates, RCRC), Sarah Deslauriers (Director of Air, Climate, and Energy Programs, California Association of Sanitation Agencies), Thomas Jordan (CEO, Scotts Valley Energy Corp), and Julia Levin (Executive Director, BAC).  Two of the meeting participants, BAC and RCRC, are parties in this Rulemaking.

DECISIONMAKER NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION. Nick Dahlberg, Energy Advisor to President Alice Reynolds logs an ex parte meeting with Small Business Utility Advocates on December 13, 2024 at 1:30 pm.
Decision D2412035 - Decision on 2024 Renewables Portfolio Standard Procurement Plans. Rulemaking 24-01-017 remains open.

REPORT ON EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4of the California Public Utilities Commissions Rules of Practice and Procedure, Small Business Utility Advocates (SBUA) reports that on Friday, December 13, 2024, from approximately 10:00 to 10:30, Ariel Strauss, Regulatory Counsel for SBUA, met by video conference with Amanda Singh Birmingham, Advisor to Commissioner Darcie Houck. The substance of the conversation recounted SBUAs arguments presented in Opening Comments on the Proposed Decision, filed December 5, 2024, that (a) Lessons Learned sections of RPS Plans must be more robust, and particularly that Southern California Edison Co. and San Diego Gas & Electric Co.s Draft 2024RPS Plans must be revised, and (b) that RPS Plans must not present BioMAT,  ReMAT and under-contract RPS projects as expected to deliver 100% of nameplate capacity when data responses from the investor-owned utilities establishes that such projects do not deliver at that level. Mr. Strauss requested that the Proposed Decision (pp. 23, 25) be corrected in these respects.

REPORT ON EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the California Public Utilities Commission Rules of Practice and Procedure, Small Business Utility Advocates (SBUA) reports that on Friday, December 13, 2024, from approximately 2:00-2:30PM, Ariel Strauss, Regulatory Counsel for SBUA met by video conference with Kpurtney Vaccaro, Advisor to Commissioner Karen Douglas.  The substance of the conversation addressed SBUAs contribution to the Proposed Decsions denial of investor owned utilities request to eliminate the advice letter pre-approval protest or shorter term REC transaction (pp 18-20) and tracked the slides provided by SBUA to Ms. Vaccaro, which are attached hereto as Attachment A.

AMERICAN CLEAN POWER  CALIFORNIA NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the California Public Utilities Commissions (Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, American Clean Power  California (ACP-California) hereby gives notice of the following ex parte meeting: On April 16, 2024, beginning at 12:00 p.m., Alex Jackson, Director of ACP-California, and Brian Biering, Attorney for ACP-California, met with Maria Sotero, Interim Chief of Staff and Jake McDermott, Advisor to Commissioner John Reynolds.  The meeting took place by Webex and lasted approximately thirty minutes. ACP-California requested the meeting as a follow-up to Commissioner Reynolds request at the Prehearing Conference for party feedback regarding coordination of the Renewables Portfolio Standard (RPS) and Integrated Resource Planning (IRP) proceeding.1  ACP-California discussed the recent IRP Preferred System Plan decision and the 25 MMT Core Portfolio results showing a need for RPS-eligible resources in excess of the minimum RPS percentages.
